Name: Default Endpoint DLP Policy Rule - Low Volume
Identity: FFO.extest.microsoft.com/Microsoft Exchange Hosted Organizations/MngEnvMCAP219373.onmicrosoft.com/Configuration/Default Endpoint DLP Policy Rule - Low Volume
Comment: "This rule is matched if 1 to 9 credit card numbers are detected in a file when a user performs certain device-related activities. When detected within a 24-hour period, the activity is only audited (not blocked). Admins won't receive alerts."

Name: Default Endpoint DLP Policy Rule - High Volume
Identity: FFO.extest.microsoft.com/Microsoft Exchange Hosted Organizations/MngEnvMCAP219373.onmicrosoft.com/Configuration/Default Endpoint DLP Policy Rule - High Volume
Comment: 'This rule is matched if 10 or more credit card numbers are detected in a file when a user performs certain device-related activities. When detected within a 24-hour period, the activity is only audited (not blocked), and admins will be alerted in email.'

Name: EndpointDevices Content matches U.S HIPAA Enhanced Default Rule
Identity: FFO.extest.microsoft.com/Microsoft Exchange Hosted Organizations/MngEnvMCAP219373.onmicrosoft.com/Configuration/EndpointDevices Content matches U.S HIPAA Enhanced Default Rule
Comment: 'Helps detect the presence of information subject to United States Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). This rule will detect specific combinations of PII Identifiers (such as SSN, DEA Numbers, and U.S addresses), specific ICD-9/10 Code descriptions, and full person names. We have also enhanced this template with Trainable Classifier Business-Healthcare which can detect healthcare and medical content in your tenant such as Medical records, Health benefits documents, Insurance forms, Prior authorizations and referral forms.'

Name: EndpointDevices Content matches Source Code Default Rule
Identity: FFO.extest.microsoft.com/Microsoft Exchange Hosted Organizations/MngEnvMCAP219373.onmicrosoft.com/Configuration/EndpointDevices Content matches Source Code Default Rule
Comment: 'By leveraging the Trainable Classifier Source Code, this rule detects items that contain a set of instructions and statements written computer programming languages on GitHub: ActionScript, C, C#, C++, Clojure, CoffeeScript, Go, Haskell, Java, JavaScript, Lua, MATLAB, Objective-C, Perl, PHP, Python, R, Ruby, Scala, Shell, Swift, TeX, Vim Script. Detects content in .msg, .as, .h, .c, .cs, .cc, .cpp, .hpp, .cxx, .hh, .c++, .clj, .edn, .cljc, .cljs, .coffee, .litcoffee, .go, .hs, .lhs, .java, .jar, .js, .mjs, .lua, .m, .mm, .pl, .pm, .t, .xs, .pod, .php, .phar, .php4, .pyc, .R, .r, .rda, .RData, .rds, .rb, .scala, .sc, .sh, .swift files'

Name: EndpointDevices Content Contains Intellectual Property
Identity: FFO.extest.microsoft.com/Microsoft Exchange Hosted Organizations/MngEnvMCAP219373.onmicrosoft.com/Configuration/EndpointDevices Content Contains Intellectual Property
Comment: 'Helps to detect content containg intellectual property by leveraging several Trainable clasifiers. Namely Project Documents, Mergers & Acquistions (M&A), Software code & design, Network security information, and other Strategic Business Documents'
